Implement a class MovingAverage:

Constructor: MovingAverage(int size)
Method: double next(int val) â€” adds the next value and returns the current moving average of the last size values.




Use a queue to track the last size elements.
Use a running sum to calculate the average efficiently.
When the queue size exceeds size, pop the oldest element and subtract it from the sum.



class MovingAverage {
private:
    queue<int> window;
    int maxSize;
    double sum;

public:
    MovingAverage(int size) {
        maxSize = size;
        sum = 0;
    }

    double next(int val) {
        if (window.size() == maxSize) {
            sum -= window.front();
            window.pop();
        }

        window.push(val);
        sum += val;

        return sum / window.size();
    }
};
